Core data science libraries:

pandas — for loading, cleaning and manipulating the dataset
numpy — for numerical calculations
matplotlib — for creating charts and plots
seaborn — for nicer statistical visualizations
openpyxl — for reading the Excel dataset files

Machine learning:

scikit-learn — for Logistic Regression, Random Forest, StandardScaler, and model evaluation metrics
xgboost — for the XGBoost classifier
joblib — for saving and loading the trained model

CLV modeling:

lifetimes — for the BG/NBD and Gamma-Gamma probabilistic models

Dashboard:

streamlit — for the interactive web dashboard

API:

fastapi — for building the REST API
uvicorn — the server that runs the FastAPI application
requests — for the dashboard to call the API

Development environment:

jupyter — for the interactive notebooks where all analysis was done
anaconda — the Python distribution that managed everything
